title: Integrated BerryMotesGallery
message:
Integrated BerryMotesGallery

A few changes:

- BerryMotesGallery is now part of BerryMotesApp. No external viewer
  necessary

- NSFW emotes removed. Because of this there is also a new sync server.

- Added option to report emotes

- Logfiles are now uploaded to the api server, not just send via mail.

- Subreddit list is now downloaded from the sync server. Because of this
  we can also show how big a subreddit is and if it was added recently.
  Fixes #1

title: Reset last sync date of all subreddits if settings are modified
message: Reset last sync date of all subreddits if settings are modified

title: Sync on a per subreddit basis
message:
Sync on a per subreddit basis

Emote list is now saved per subreddit, this allows the app to
only download and load emote lists that are set to sync. It also
allows us to process the emote list in smaller batches, improving
memory usage.

Subreddit sync now run concurrently in up to 4 thread to improve
sync performance.

Subreddit information is now also saved, allowing consumers to
filter based on subreddit

title: Fixed sync all
message:
Fixed sync all

Even when all is enabled, the sync would skip subreddits that
where not in the list of enabled subreddits because there was a
typo in the ALL_KEY for the CheckListPreference.

title: Added logback
message:
Added logback

logback allows logging to file and logcat simultanously (and
many other log destinations actually). If we need to we can
asks users to send the log files that logback generates to
troubleshoot sync errors.
